<title>USA: Pier 1 files for $50 mln debt offering.</title>
<headline>Pier 1 files for $50 mln debt offering.</headline>
<dateline>FORT WORTH, Texas 1996-08-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Specialty retailer Pier 1 Imports Inc said Friday it filed a registration statement for a public offering of $50 million of convertible subordinated notes due 2006.</p>
<p>The terms of the notes have not yet been established.</p>
<p>Jeffries &amp; Co Inc and Forum Capital Markets LP will act as co-managing underwriters for the offering.</p>
<p>The company said proceeds from the sale will be used to retire outstanding debt and for working capital and other corporate purposes.</p>
<p>--New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610.</p>
</text>
